[debug] [2026-02-28T08:43:13.357Z] >>> [apiv2][body] POST https://cloudaicompanion.googleapis.com/v1beta/projects/barangay-ncd-monitoring/locations/global/instances/default:completeTask {"input":{"messages":[{"content":"Create a mutation to populate the database with some seed data.","author":"USER"}]},"experienceContext":{"experience":"/appeco/firebase/fdc-query-generator"},"clientContext":{"additionalContext":{"@type":"type.googleapis.com/google.cloud.cloudaicompanion.v1main.FirebaseChatRequestContext","fdcInfo":{"fdcServiceName":"projects/barangay-ncd-monitoring/locations/us-east4/services/barangay-non-communicable-disease-ncd-monitoring-health-mapping","requiresQuery":true}}}}
[debug] [2026-02-28T08:43:19.286Z] <<< [apiv2][status] POST https://cloudaicompanion.googleapis.com/v1beta/projects/barangay-ncd-monitoring/locations/global/instances/default:completeTask 200
[debug] [2026-02-28T08:43:19.286Z] <<< [apiv2][body] POST https://cloudaicompanion.googleapis.com/v1beta/projects/barangay-ncd-monitoring/locations/global/instances/default:completeTask {"output":{"messages":[{"content":"Hello there! Gemini in Firebase here, ready to help you craft those GraphQL operations for your NCD Monitoring app. Based on your schema and the need for proper authentication, here are four operations:\n\nFirst up, a query to list all non-communicable disease types. This is information that's generally safe for anyone to view, so we'll make it publicly accessible.\n\n```graphql\nquery ListNCDTypes @auth(level: PUBLIC, insecureReason: \"This operation is safe to expose to the public as it lists general NCD types.\") {\n  nCDTypes {\n    id\n    name\n    description\n  }\n}\n```\n\nNext, let's create a query to fetch details about a specific resident. This kind of personal data should only be accessible to authenticated users.\n\n```graphql\nquery GetResidentDetails($residentId: UUID!) @auth(level: USER, insecureReason: \"This operation is safe to expose to all logged in users as it fetches details for a specific resident ID.\") {\n  resident(id: $residentId) {\n    id\n    firstName\n    lastName\n    birthDate\n    address\n    barangayId\n    contactNumber\n    email\n    gender\n    middleName\n    createdAt\n  }\n}\n```\n\nNow for a mutation! Let's say we want to record a new diagnosis for a resident. This clearly needs to be restricted to authenticated users. We'll also include the current timestamp for `createdAt` and use `auth.uid` as the `loggerId` to track which user made the entry, assuming a user role exists to log diagnoses.\n\n```graphql\nmutation RecordNewDiagnosis($residentId: UUID!, $ncdTypeId: UUID!, $diagnosisDate: Date!, $status: String!, $notes: String) @auth(level: USER) {\n  diagnosis_insert(data: {\n    residentId: $residentId,\n    ncdTypeId: $ncdTypeId,\n    diagnosisDate: $diagnosisDate,\n    status: $status,\n    notes: $notes,\n    createdAt_expr: \"request.time\"\n  }) {\n    id\n  }\n}\n```\n\nFinally, let's make a mutation to update a resident's contact information. This also requires user authentication.\n\n```graphql\nmutation UpdateResidentContact($residentId: UUID!, $contactNumber: String, $email: String) @auth(level: USER) {\n  resident_update(id: $residentId, data: {\n    contactNumber: $contactNumber,\n    email: $email\n  }) {\n    id\n  }\n}\n```\n\nThese operations give you a solid start for your app!\n\nTo explore further, you might want to ask:\n\n*   How can I filter `HealthEvent` records by event type for a specific resident?\n*   How can I implement role-based access control for certain mutations, like allowing only \"admin\" users to delete records?\n*   Can you show me an example of how to insert a new user with `username`, `passwordHash`, and `role`?","author":"model"}]},"outputDataContext":{"additionalContext":{"@type":"type.googleapis.com/google.cloud.cloudaicompanion.v1main.ChatOutputDataContext","relatedContent":{}}},"attributionContext":{"citationMetadata":{}}}
[debug] [2026-02-28T08:43:22.801Z] <<< [apiv2][status] POST https://cloudaicompanion.googleapis.com/v1beta/projects/barangay-ncd-monitoring/locations/global/instances/default:completeTask 200
[debug] [2026-02-28T08:43:22.801Z] <<< [apiv2][body] POST https://cloudaicompanion.googleapis.com/v1beta/projects/barangay-ncd-monitoring/locations/global/instances/default:completeTask {"output":{"messages":[{"content":"Here's a mutation to populate your database with some seed data for `NCDType`, `User`, `Resident`, `Diagnosis`, and `HealthEvent` tables. I've used `_upsertMany` to handle cases where you might run this multiple times and want to update existing entries or insert new ones.\n\n```graphql\nmutation SeedDatabase @transaction @auth(level: USER, insecureReason: \"This mutation is for seeding data and should only be run by authenticated users.\") {\n  nCDType_upsertMany(data: [\n    {\n      id: \"b2d3e4f5-a1b2-c3d4-e5f6-7890abcdeff1\",\n      name: \"Hypertension\",\n      description: \"High blood pressure\"\n    },\n    {\n      id: \"b2d3e4f5-a1b2-c3d4-e5f6-7890abcdeff2\",\n      name: \"Diabetes Mellitus\",\n      description: \"Chronic disease affecting how your body turns food into energy\"\n    },\n    {\n      id: \"b2d3e4f5-a1b2-c3d4-e5f6-7890abcdeff3\",\n      name: \"Asthma\",\n      description: \"A condition in which your airways narrow and swell\"\n    }\n  ])\n  user_upsertMany(data: [\n    {\n      id: \"a1b2c3d4-e5f6-7890-a1b2-c3d4e5f67891\",\n      username: \"adminuser\",\n      passwordHash: \"hashedpassword1\",\n      role: \"admin\",\n      displayName: \"Admin User\",\n      email: \"admin@example.com\",\n      createdAt_expr: \"request.time\"\n    },\n    {\n      id: \"a1b2c3d4-e5f6-7890-a1b2-c3d4e5f67892\",\n      username: \"healthworker\",\n      passwordHash: \"hashedpassword2\",\n      role: \"health_worker\",\n      displayName: \"Health Worker\",\n      email: \"worker@example.com\",\n      createdAt_expr: \"request.time\"\n    }\n  ])\n  resident_upsertMany(data: [\n    {\n      id: \"f1e2d3c4-b5a6-7890-1234-56789abcdef1\",\n      firstName: \"Juan\",\n      lastName: \"Dela Cruz\",\n      middleName: \"Santos\",\n      birthDate: \"1980-01-15\",\n      address: \"123 Main St, Barangay A\",\n      barangayId: \"BA001\",\n      createdAt_expr: \"request.time\",\n      gender: \"Male\",\n      contactNumber: \"09171234567\",\n      email: \"juan.delacruz@example.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      id: \"f1e2d3c4-b5a6-7890-1234-56789abcdef2\",\n      firstName: \"Maria\",\n      lastName: \"Santos\",\n      middleName: \"Reyes\",\n      birthDate: \"1975-05-20\",\n      address: \"456 Elm St, Barangay A\",\n      barangayId: \"BA001\",\n      createdAt_expr: \"request.time\",\n      gender: \"Female\",\n      contactNumber: \"09187654321\",\n      email: \"maria.santos@example.com\"\n    }\n  ])\n  diagnosis_upsertMany(data: [\n    {\n      residentId: \"f1e2d3c4-b5a6-7890-1234-56789abcdef1\",\n      ncdTypeId: \"b2d3e4f5-a1b2-c3d4-e5f6-7890abcdeff1\",\n      diagnosisDate: \"2022-03-10\",\n      status: \"Active\",\n      createdAt_expr: \"request.time\",\n      notes: \"Initial diagnosis, advised lifestyle changes.\"\n    },\n    {\n      residentId: \"f1e2d3c4-b5a6-7890-1234-56789abcdef2\",\n      ncdTypeId: \"b2d3e4f5-a1b2-c3d4-e5f6-7890abcdeff2\",\n      diagnosisDate: \"2021-11-01\",\n      status: \"Controlled\",\n      createdAt_expr: \"request.time\",\n      notes: \"On medication, regular check-ups.\"\n    }\n  ])\n  healthEvent_upsertMany(data: [\n    {\n      residentId: \"f1e2d3c4-b5a6-7890-1234-56789abcdef1\",\n      loggerId: \"a1b2c3d4-e5f6-7890-a1b2-c3d4e5f67892\",\n      eventType: \"Blood Pressure Reading\",\n      eventDate: \"2023-10-26\",\n      createdAt_expr: \"request.time\",\n      details: \"BP: 140/90 mmHg\",\n      outcome: \"High\"\n    },\n    {\n      residentId: \"f1e2d3c4-b5a6-7890-1234-56789abcdef2\",\n      loggerId: \"a1b2c3d4-e5f6-7890-a1b2-c3d4e5f67892\",\n      eventType: \"Glucose Test\",\n      eventDate: \"2023-10-25\",\n      createdAt_expr: \"request.time\",\n      details: \"Fasting blood sugar: 130 mg/dL\",\n      outcome: \"Elevated\"\n    }\n  ])\n}\n```","author":"model"}]},"outputDataContext":{"additionalContext":{"@type":"type.googleapis.com/google.cloud.cloudaicompanion.v1main.ChatOutputDataContext","relatedContent":{}}},"attributionContext":{"citationMetadata":{}}}
